The function `UnusedSubroutineSearchAmsiPattern` is supposed to search for a specific pattern of byte sequences within a specified memory address range. Here's how you can complete the code:

```c
ULONGLONG UnusedSubroutineSearchAmsiPattern(PBYTE Address, DWORD Size, PBYTE Pattern, DWORD PatternSize)
{
    ULONGLONG AmsiAddress = 0LL;
    for (ULONGLONG i = 0; i < Size - PatternSize; i++)
    {
        if (memcmp(Address + i, Pattern, PatternSize) == 0)
        {
            AmsiAddress = (ULONGLONG)(Address + i);
            break;
        }
    }
    return AmsiAddress;
}
```

This function iterates over the memory address range specified by `Address` and `Size`. It checks each byte to see if it matches the pattern specified by `Pattern` and `PatternSize`. If a match is found, it returns the address of the match. If no match is found, it returns 0.

